cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the problem of predicting similarity between handwritten document images, which involves image processing, computer vision, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves text mining and information retrieval, which suggests the category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing and text analysis, which suggests the category cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper proposes a convolutional neural network (CNN) based feature descriptor, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves the use of algorithms and techniques for matching and mining in image collections, which suggests the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
